==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentagon
<hw>Pen"ta*gon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>penta`gwnon</grk>; <grk>penta-</grk> (see <er>Penta-</er>) +
<grk>gwni`a</grk> angle: cf. L. <ets>pentagonium</ets>, F.
<ets>pentagone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A plane figure
having five angles, and, consequently, five sides; any figure having
five angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Regular pentagon</b></col>, <cd>a pentagon in which the
angles are all equal, and the sides all equal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentagonal</ent>⟦br⟧
